AttributeList.Text: The high side is the evaporator discharge temp & pressure, in gas phase The low side, should be the evaporator suction temp & pressure, in liquid phase, but: - the condenser discharge pressure is used as it is the only pressure reading in that part of the system. - the expansion valve temperature is used "We use the entalpy of the liquid before the expansion valve instead of the one before the evaporator, because the pressure and quality of the fluid before the evaporator is uncertain, but it is known before the expansion valve and the expansion valve itself does not alter the enthalpy very much. "
